    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>The radio receive sensitivity was fine down to 100 dBm although the volume 
in the speaker was low. However, transmit in SSB didn’t make it past a 
watt and we only got about 4W for the carrier on AM. Probably something
wrong with the audio path as the radio uses the same circuit in both 
rx and tx directions. That also explains the low speaker volume.</p>

<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/06/codan6924-5.jpeg">
